  });
});```

**Explanation:**

* In the `cypress.config.js` file, we set the `DOCKER_IMAGE` and `DOCKER_CONTAINER_PORT` environment variables to use a Docker image and port for the application under test.
* We enable screenshot capture by setting `screenshotOnRunFailure` to `true` and specifying the screenshot folder as `cypress/screenshots`.
* We set the base URL to the Docker container port using the `baseUrl` property.
* We set the default timeout to 10 seconds using the `defaultTimeout` property.
* We set the reporter to use the Mocha reporter and configure the reporter options to print files, summary, and details.

* In the `cypress/support/index.js` file, we add a command to take a screenshot on failure using the `on('fail')` event. We get the current test context using `error.context` and take a screenshot using the `screenshot` method.

* In the `cypress/integration/example.spec.js` file, we define two tests: one that passes and one that fails. The failing test will trigger the screenshot capture on failure.

Run the tests using `npx cypress run` and navigate to the `cypress/screenshots` folder to see the captured screenshots.

Here is a C++ function that takes a reference to a `std::string` containing markdown formatted text and returns a `std::string` containing HTML formatted text:

```cpp
#include <string>
#include <boost/algorithm/string/replace.hpp>

std::string markdownToHtml(const std::string& markdown) {
    // Replace markdown headers with HTML headers
    std::string html = markdown;
    boost::replace_all(html, "# ", "<h1>");
    boost::replace_all(html, "## ", "<h2>");
    boost::replace_all(html, "### ", "<h3>");
    boost::replace_all(html, "#### ", "<h4>");
    boost::replace_all(html, "##### ", "<h5>");
    boost::replace_all(html, "###### ", "<h6>");

    // Replace markdown bold text with HTML bold text
    boost::replace_all(html, "**", "<b>");
    boost::replace_all(html, "**", "</b>");

    // Replace markdown italic text with HTML italic text
    boost::replace_all(html, "*", "<i>");
    boost::replace_all(html, "*", "</i>");

    // Replace markdown links with HTML links
    boost::replace_all(html, "[", "<a href='");
    boost::replace_all(html, "]", "'");

    // Replace markdown images with HTML images
    boost::replace_all(html, "!\[", "<img src='");
    boost::replace_all(html, "\(", "'");
    boost::replace_all(html, "\]", "'");

    return html;
}
```

In this function, we use the Boost library's `replace_all` function to replace markdown syntax with HTML syntax. 

Here's a breakdown of what each replacement does:

- Headers: Replaces `#` followed by a space with `<h1>`, `##` followed by a space with `<h2>`, and so on.
- Bold text: Replaces `**` with `<b>` and `**` with `</b>`.
- Italic text: Replaces `*` with `<i>` and `*` with `</i>`.
- Links: Replaces `[` with `<a href='` and `]` with `'`.
- Images: Replaces `![` with `<img src='` and `(` with `'`.

Note that this is a basic implementation and may not cover all edge cases or handle all possible markdown syntax.

